                  </persName>
            , and while the Prosecutor's Maid (the Prisoner) was gone out, they went up Stairs, and 
               <persName id="t17291015-80-person451">
                  Ann 
                  William 
               <interp inst="t17291015-80-person451" type="surname" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17291015-80-person451" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17291015-80-person451" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             s took the Watch off from the Chest of Drawers while a Gentleman lay asleep in the Room, and she stood 3 or 4 Stairs below, and 
               <persName id="t17291015-80-person452">
                  Ann 
                  Williams 
               <interp inst="t17291015-80-person452" type="surname" value="Williams"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17291015-80-person452" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17291015-80-person452" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
